n be proved by `simp`\nusing later, more general simp lemmas. In that case, the following reasons might be arguments for\nthe early lemma to be tagged `@[simp high]` (rather than `@[simp, nolint simpNF]` or\nun-`@[simp]`ed):\n1. There is a significant portion of the library which needs the early lemma to be available via\n  `simp` and which doesn't have access to the more general lemmas.\n2. The more general lemmas have more complicated typeclass assumptions, causing rewrites with them\n  to be slower.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/NNRat/Defs.html#LibraryNote.specialised_high_priority_simp_lemma","kind":"def","line":44,"name":"LibraryNote.specialised_high_priority_simp_lemma","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Data/NNRat/Defs.lean#L44-L53"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.Order.Group.Unbundled.Int","Mathlib.Algebra.Order.Nonneg.Basic","Mathlib.Algebra.Order.Ring.Unbundled.Rat","Mathlib.Algebra.Ring.Rat","Mathlib.Data.Set.Operations","Mathlib.Order.Bounds.Defs","Mathlib.Order.GaloisConnection.Defs"],"instances":[{"className":"PosMulMono","name":"Rat.instPosMulMono","typeNames":["Rat"]},{"className":"CommSemiring","name":"instCommSemiringNNRat","typeNames":["NNRat"]},{"className":"AddCancelCommMonoid","name":"instAddCancelCommMonoidNNRat","typeNames":["NNRat"]},{"className":"LinearOrder","name":"instLinearOrderNNRat","typeNames":["NNRat"]},{"className":"Sub","name":"instSubNNRat","typeNames":["NNRat"]},{"className":"Inhabited","name":"instInhabitedNNRat","typeNames":["NNRat"]},{"className":"Nontrivial","name":"NNRat.instNontrivial","typeNames":["NNRat"]},{"className":"OrderBot","name":"NNRat.instOrderBot","typeNames":["NNRat"]},{"className":"CharZero","name":"NNRat.instCharZero","typeNames":["NNRat"]},{"className":"CanLift","name":"NNRat.canLift","typeNames":["Rat","NNRat","NNRat.cast"]}],"name":"Mathlib.Data.NNRat.Defs"}